  title: "Full Stack Software Engineer",
  description: "<h3>About Loop &amp; Tie:</h3> <p>Loop &amp; Tie is an engagement platform helping businesses connect with customers and employees through gifting. Our platform offers businesses the data they need to assess ROI and the functionally they need to easily integrate gifting into their acquisition and retention programs. We envision a world where showing gratitude is a core business activity, and we’re the engine powering millions of acts of appreciation.</p> <p>We are a fast-paced, user-first technology company that’s passionate about building responsibly. We believe the future of work is a regenerative corporate environment where giving and receiving are in balance. When we build we don’t just think about maximizing profit—we believe you can be wildly profitable while also being socially and environmentally conscious. Our fully-remote team is comprised of 16 awesome people (and quickly growing!) in New York, Texas, and North Carolina. We are committed to developing diverse teams. Our current team is 35% POC and 60% women, and we continuously strive to add more diversity on our team.</p> <h3>Job Requirements and Responsibilities:</h3> <ul> <li>Strong front-end experience and familiarity working in a Rails system (you're full stack, but leaning more toward front-end)</li> <li>Design, build, and test end-to-end features using Rails</li> <li>Write comprehensive tests</li> <li>Create and maintain APIs</li> <li>Plan and maintain a product long-term</li> <li>Plan stories and resolve assigned tickets in Pivotal Tracker</li> <li>Participate in code reviews; follow and assist in the development of Loop and Tie's coding guidelines</li> </ul> <h3>Candidate Qualifications:</h3> <ul> <li>Familiarity with our stack: Rails sitting on top of Heroku using Postgres, Elasticsearch, Redis, and a variety of AWS services</li> <li>3+ years of professional software development experience for the web</li> <li>Experience deploying and supporting code in production</li> <li>Knowledge of development best practices (agile methodologies, code reviews, Javascript testing frameworks)</li> <li>Experience in full life-cycle development of web applications</li> <li>You have startup experience and you enjoy working with small teams</li> <li>Experience with a web frameworks and ORMs, like Rails or Django</li> <li>Experience with Angular, React, or plain old Javascript (ES6+ preferred)</li> </ul> <h3>What You Get:</h3> <ul> <li>Fully remote role, so you can work from home</li> <li>3 weeks vacation and a generous company holiday calendar</li> <li>Wellness and education benefits</li> <li>Dental and health insurance</li> <li>Stock options</li> </ul> ",
